.\"
.TH GET 1 "2026-04-14" "get 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH NAME
get \- get anything from your computer using natural language
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B get
.RI \(dq query \(dq
.RI [ flags ]
.br
.B get set
.I option
.RI [ value ]
.br
.B get config
.RI [ \-\-reset | \-\- option ]
.br
.B get cache
.RI [ \-\-clean | "\-\-unset \(dq" query \(dq ]
.br
.B get log
.RI [ \-\-clean ]
.br
.B get get
.RI [ \-\-intro | \-\-version | \-\-license | \-\-github ]
.br
.B get version
.br
.B get isok
.br
.B get help
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B get
is a small command-line tool that uses a large language model (LLM) to
generate shell commands from natural-language queries and executes them
to retrieve information from your device.
It is designed to perform
.B read-only
operations only.
Every generated command passes through multiple safety layers before
execution.
.PP
.B get
is compatible with any OpenAI-API-compatible endpoint and ships with
bundled high-performance command-line tools
.RB ( rg ,
.BR fd ,
.BR sg ,
.BR pmc ,
.BR treepp / tree ,
.BR tokei ,
.BR lua ,
.BR bat ,
.BR mdcat )
that are automatically available to generated commands.
A lightweight edition without the bundled
.I bin/
directory is also available; in that case only system-installed tools
are used.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH COMMANDS
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS "Query (default)"
.BI "get \(dq" "query" "\(dq [" "flags" "]"
.PP
Sends
.I query
to the configured LLM, which generates a shell command.
The command is validated, optionally double-checked and confirmed, then
executed.
The output is either displayed directly or interpreted by the LLM,
depending on the model's annotation.
.PP
See
.B QUERY FLAGS
below for per-invocation overrides.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS set
.BI "get set " "option" " [" "value" "]"
.PP
Sets a single configuration option.
Omitting
.I value
resets the option to its default (for booleans and integers) or clears
it (for strings).
See
.B SET OPTIONS
for the full list.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS config
.B get config
.PP
Displays all current configuration values.
.TP
.B \-\-reset
Resets all configuration to default values and clears the stored API key.
.TP
.BI \-\- option
Displays the current value of a single option, where
.I option
is any name from the
.B SET OPTIONS
table (e.g.\&
.BR \-\-model ,
.BR \-\-timeout ).
The
.B \-\-key
flag shows the key status with the value masked.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS cache
.B get cache
.PP
Displays cache status: whether caching is enabled, entry count,
configured limits, and file location.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Removes all cached entries.
.TP
.BI "\-\-unset \(dq" query \(dq
Removes all cache entries whose query text matches
.I query
(case-insensitive).
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS log
.B get log
.PP
Displays log status: whether logging is enabled, configured maximum
entries, entry count, file location, and file size.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Removes all entries from the log file.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS get
.B get get
.PP
Displays all application information (version, introduction, license,
GitHub URL).
.TP
.B \-\-intro
Displays the one-line introduction.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Displays the version string (equivalent to
.BR "get version" ).
.TP
.B \-\-license
Displays the SPDX license identifier.
.TP
.B \-\-github
Displays the GitHub repository URL.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS version
.B get version
.PP
Prints the version string and exits.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS isok
.B get isok
.PP
Verifies that the current configuration is ready for use.
Checks that the API key, URL, and model are all set, then sends a
lightweight probe request to the LLM endpoint.
Exits with code 0 on success, 1 on failure.
.\"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SS help
.B get help
.PP
Displays comprehensive usage help.
Also triggered by
.B \-\-help
and
.BR \-h .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH QUERY FLAGS
Per-invocation flags that override the persisted configuration for a
single query.
These flags are placed after the query string.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Bypass the cache for this query.
.TP
.B \-\-cache
Force cache lookup and storage for this query.
.TP
.B \-\-manual\-confirm
Prompt for confirmation before executing the generated command.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-manual\-confirm
Skip the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-double\-check
Enable the second LLM safety review.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-double\-check
Skip the second LLM safety review.
.TP
.B \-\-instance
Use fast single-call mode; output is always shown directly.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-instance
Use multi-step mode with output-mode detection.
.TP
.B \-\-hide\-process
Suppress intermediate output (progress, commands).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-hide\-process
Show intermediate output.
.TP
.BI \-\-model " name"
Override the LLM model for this query.
.TP
.BI \-\-style " mode"
Override the output style for this query.
.I mode
is one of
.BR simp ,
.BR std ,
or
.BR vivid .
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " seconds"
Override the request timeout for this query.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SET OPTIONS
The following options can be configured with
.BR "get set" .
Integer options accept
.B false
to disable the feature entirely (equivalent to 0).
An empty value resets the option to its default.
.TP
.BI "key " string
LLM API key.
Stored using platform-specific secure storage (Linux: file permissions
0600; Windows: DPAPI).
Default: empty.
.TP
.BI "url " URL
LLM API endpoint URL.
Default:
.IR https://api.poe.com/v1 .
.TP
.BI "model " string
LLM model name.
Default:
.IR gpt\-5.3\-codex .
.TP
.BI "manual\-confirm " bool
Whether to require manual confirmation before executing generated
commands.
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "double\-check " bool
Whether to invoke the model for a second safety review of the generated
command.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "instance " bool
Whether to ask the model to reply as quickly as possible (single-call
mode; output is always shown directly).
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "timeout " "integer | false"
Timeout for a single API request, in seconds.
Default:
.IR 300 .
.TP
.BI "max\-token " "integer | false"
Maximum token consumption per request.
Default:
.IR 20480 .
.TP
.BI "command\-pattern " regex
Regex pattern matching forbidden commands; execution is rejected if the
generated command matches.
Default: built-in blocklist (see
.BR SAFETY ).
.TP
.BI "system\-prompt " string
Custom system prompt appended to the LLM context.
Default: empty.
.TP
.BI "shell " string
The shell used to execute commands.
Default:
.I powershell
on Windows;
.I bash
on Linux.
.TP
.BI "log " bool
Whether to log each request and execution.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "hide\-process " bool
Whether to hide intermediate steps and only output the final result.
Default:
.IR false .
.TP
.BI "cache " bool
Whether to enable response caching.
Default:
.IR true .
.TP
.BI "cache\-expiry " "integer | false"
Number of days before a cache entry expires.
Default:
.IR 30 .
.TP
.BI "cache\-max\-entries " "integer | false"
Maximum number of entries retained in the cache.
Default:
.IR 1000 .
.TP
.BI "log\-max\-entries " "integer | false"
Maximum number of entries retained in the log.
Default:
.IR 1000 .
.TP
.BI "style " "simp | std | vivid"
Output style.
See
.BR "OUTPUT STYLES" .
Default:
.IR std .
.TP
.BI "external\-display " bool
Whether to use
.BR bat (1)
and
.BR mdcat (1)
for syntax-highlighted and Markdown output rendering in
.B std
and
.B vivid
modes.
Default:
.IR true .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SAFETY
.B get
is designed to perform read-only operations only.
The LLM is prompted with strict read-only constraints, and every
generated command undergoes multiple layers of validation before
execution:
.TP
.B 1. Dangerous-command check
A built-in safety check rejects commands containing known destructive
operations before they can execute.
This check runs independently of any
.B command\-pattern
configuration.
.IP
Blocked commands include:
.BR rm ,
.BR rmdir ,
.BR del ,
.BR rd ,
.BR erase ,
.BR mv ,
.BR move ,
.BR cp ,
.BR copy ,
.BR mkdir ,
.BR md ,
.BR touch ,
.BR chmod ,
.BR chown ,
.BR chgrp ,
.BR mkfs ,
.BR dd ,
.BR format ,
.BR fdisk ,
.BR kill ,
.BR killall ,
.BR pkill ,
.BR shutdown ,
.BR reboot ,
.BR halt ,
.BR poweroff ,
.BR passwd ,
.BR useradd ,
.BR userdel ,
.BR usermod ,
.BR groupadd ,
.BR groupdel ,
.BR Set\-Content ,
.BR New\-Item ,
.BR Remove\-Item ,
.BR Move\-Item ,
.BR Rename\-Item ,
.BR Clear\-Content ,
and
.BR Add\-Content .
.TP
.B 2. Double-check
(Default: enabled.)
A second LLM safety review of the generated command.
The reviewer model assesses whether the command is strictly read-only
and safe, and may revise the command or reject it outright.
.TP
.B 3. Command-pattern validation
Optional regex matching via the
.B command\-pattern
setting.
When a custom pattern is set,
.B get
checks whether the pattern adequately covers common dangerous commands
and displays a warning if not.
.TP
.B 4. Manual confirmation
Optional interactive y/N prompt via the
.B manual\-confirm
setting.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH MODEL STRENGTH
.B get
executes shell commands generated by the LLM on your device.
A sufficiently capable model is the foundation of safety.
At startup,
.B get
checks the configured model name against a built-in whitelist of known
high-performance models and displays a warning if the model is not
recognised.
.PP
Known strong models include:
GPT 5+ (including CodeX variants),
Claude Opus/Sonnet 3.5+,
Claude 3.7+ (by version),
Gemini 3+,
Grok 4+,
GLM 4.7+,
MiniMax 2.7+,
DeepSeek (full versions),
and OpenAI o-series 3+.
Reduced-capability variants (Mini, Nano, Lite, Haiku, Flash, etc.) and
unsupported families trigger the warning.
The warning is advisory and does not block execution.
.PP
Model names are normalised before comparison \(em case differences and
underscores vs hyphens are handled transparently
.RB ( Claude_Opus_4.6
and
.B claude\-opus\-4.6
are equivalent).
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH OUTPUT STYLES
.B get
supports three output styles, configured via
.BR "get set style" :
.TP
.B simp
Plain text, no formatting.
Sections separated by blank lines.
.TP
.B std
Dividers and basic ANSI colours (default).
.TP
.B vivid
Animated spinners, bold colours, Markdown rendering via
.BR mdcat (1).
This mode is experimental.
It requires the bundled
.B mdcat
binary for Markdown rendering; if unavailable, a warning is shown
suggesting
.BR "get set style std" .
An experimental notice is displayed on each invocation.
.PP
When
.B external\-display
is enabled (default), the
.BR bat (1)
binary is used for syntax-highlighted output and
.BR mdcat (1)
is used for Markdown rendering in
.B std
and
.B vivid
modes.
If the required binaries are not found in the bundled
.I bin/
directory, a warning is emitted and output falls back to plain text.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH OUTPUT MODE
By default,
.B get
instructs the LLM to annotate its response with either
.B "<!-- DIRECT -->"
or
.BR "<!-- INTERPRET -->" .
Most queries produce direct output \(em the raw command result is shown
without an additional LLM call.
Only when the output needs summarisation or analysis does
.B get
invoke the LLM again.
In
.B instance
mode, output is always shown directly.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH CACHING
.B get
caches the final output of each query keyed by a hash of the query
text and execution context (working directory, shell, model, instance
mode, system prompt, and command pattern).
When the same query is run under the same context, the cached result is
returned immediately without making any API calls.
.PP
Before storing a new cache entry,
.B get
sends a lightweight LLM request to determine whether the result is
stable (cacheable) or volatile (not cacheable).
Volatile results \(em such as current time, CPU usage, or running
processes \(em are not cached even when caching is enabled.
.PP
To bypass the cache for a single query, use the
.B \-\-no\-cache
flag:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqyour query\(dq \-\-no\-cache
.RE
.PP
Cache parameters can be tuned with
.BR "get set cache\-expiry" ,
.BR "get set cache\-max\-entries" ,
and
.BR "get set cache" .
See
.B SET OPTIONS
for details.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH LOGGING
.B get
logs each query execution (query text, generated command, exit code,
and output preview) to a local file.
When the entry count exceeds the
.B log\-max\-entries
limit (unless disabled with
.BR false ),
the oldest entries are automatically removed.
.PP
Logging parameters can be tuned with
.B "get set log\-max\-entries"
and
.BR "get set log" .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH BUNDLED TOOLS
.B get
ships with several high-performance command-line tools in the
.I bin/
directory.
These tools are automatically available to generated commands via PATH
prepending.
.TP
.B rg
ripgrep \(em ultra-fast regex search in files.
.TP
.B fd
Fast file/directory finder.
.TP
.B sg
ast-grep \(em AST-level structural code search.
.TP
.B pmc
pack-my-code \(em code context packaging for LLM prompts.
.TP
.BR treepp " (Windows) / " tree " (Linux)"
tree++ (Windows) / classic Unix tree (Linux) \(em directory tree
listing.
.TP
.B tokei
Code statistics (lines of code by language).
.TP
.B lua
Lua 5.x interpreter for calculations and text processing.
.TP
.B bat
Syntax-highlighting cat replacement.
.TP
.B mdcat
Terminal Markdown renderer.
.PP
The LLM is made aware of these tools and will prefer them when they fit
the task.
Write-mode flags on bundled tools (e.g.\&
.BR "pmc \-o" ,
.BR "treepp /O" )
are explicitly forbidden in the prompt.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
.B get
requires a 64-bit platform (amd64 or arm64) running Windows 10+ or
Linux with kernel 6.0+.
A startup warning is shown if the runtime environment does not meet
these requirements.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH STATIC BUILDS
To produce a fully statically linked binary (no dynamic library
dependencies), build with the
.B staticBuild
flag.
This requires static OpenSSL libraries to be available on the system:
.PP
.RS
.B nim c \-d:release \-d:staticBuild src/get.nim
.RE
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GET_TEST_KEY
API key used by the test suite for live LLM connectivity tests.
.TP
.B GET_TEST_URL
API endpoint URL used by the test suite.
.TP
.B GET_TEST_MODEL
Model name used by the test suite.
.PP
These variables are only relevant when running the test suite; they are
not used during normal operation.
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/config.json
Configuration file (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/key
API key storage file (Linux, mode 0600).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/get.log
Append-only execution log (Linux).
.TP
.I ~/.config/get/cache.json
Response cache file (Linux).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/config.json
Configuration file (Windows).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/key
API key storage file (Windows, DPAPI-encrypted).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/get.log
Append-only execution log (Windows).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%/get/cache.json
Response cache file (Windows).
.TP
.IR <exe>/bin/ " or " <exe>/src/bin/
Bundled binary tools directory.
The production layout
.RI ( <exe>/bin/ )
is checked first, then the development layout
.RI ( <exe>/src/bin/ ).
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.
.TP
.B 1
Configuration error, LLM communication failure, safety check rejection,
or general error.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by Ctrl+C (SIGINT).
.TP
.I N
When a generated command exits with a non-zero code, that code is
propagated as the exit status of
.BR get .
.\"
.\" ====================================================================
.SH EXAMPLES
Retrieve system version information:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqsystem version\(dq
.RE
.PP
List code files in the current directory:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqcode in the directory\(dq
.RE
.PP
Fetch information from a URL:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqthe latest get version at https://github.com/Water\-Run/get\(dq
.RE
.PP
Bypass the cache for a single query:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqdisk usage\(dq \-\-no\-cache
.RE
.PP
Override the model and style for a single query:
.PP
.RS
.B get \(dqlist files\(dq \-\-model gpt\-5.3\-codex \-\-style vivid
.RE
.PP
Configure the API key:
.PP
.RS
.B get set key sk\-your\-api\-key
.RE
.PP
Configure the API endpoint:
.PP
.RS
.B get set url https://api.openai.com/v1
.RE
.PP
Unset the API key:
.PP
.RS
.B get set key
.RE
.PP
Disable the request timeout:
.PP
.RS
.B get set timeout false
.RE
.PP
Change the output style:
.PP
.RS
.B get set style vivid
.RE
.PP
View a single configuration option:
.PP
.RS
.B get config \-\-model
.RE
.PP
Reset all configuration to defaults:
.PP
.RS
.B get config \-\-reset
.RE
.PP
Clear the cache:
.PP
.RS
.B get cache \-\-clean
.RE
.PP
Remove a specific cached query:
.PP
.RS
.B get cache \-\-unset \(dqsystem version\(dq
.RE
.PP
Clear the log:
.PP
.RS
.B get log \-\-clean
.RE
.PP
Verify configuration readiness:
.PP
.RS
.B get isok
.RE
